90 Day Fiancé  
(Season 10)
Rebecca's C urrent Hyperfixa tion

Some of us (myself) need a succinct way to describe the concept of 90 Day Fiancé and the couples involved to those who haven't asked. This site allows for just that! (So long as you are only discussing Season 10 of the main series.)

Read More!

What do you get when you combine snow days with your parents' Amazon Prime Video subscription? Access to Season 10 of  90 Day Finacé ! I have watched previous seasons of this series as well as some of the spin-off series, but this particular season is what I have been fixated on lately. I recently tried to describe the concept of the show and the couples involved to my uncle, but it's difficult to go about it in a concise way. Violà , an organized site to do just that!

What is  90 Day  Fiancé ?

The TL;DR

90 Day Fiancé  follows the journey of international couples hoping to unite in holy matrimony. When  granted the K-1 visa, these couples have 90 days in the States to get married, otherwise, the international partner must return to their home country.

With very little time to acclimate to living in a different country, speaking and understanding a different language, and learning to live with another individual, these couples are put under extreme stress. Will they work through these hardships together, or will they be forced apart by a harsh reality?

The Couples

Messy, unhinged, and in love*.

*Subject to individual interpretation

Here, I present an extremely biased description of each couple. Hover over each bio to see my ramblings!

Jasmine and Gino

Leaving behind her two young children in Panama, Jasmine (36) uproots to be with Gino (52) in Michigan. Their relationship consists of highs (a trip to Miami) and lows (literally everything else), but love keeps them together.

I LOVE Jasmine. She is so dramatic and would likely be way too much to deal with in person, but I could look past that if she ever wanted to be friends. That said, I think she needs therapy. She's been through legitimate trauma in her life, and a relationship isn't enough to fix that. Gino doesn't have the capability of helping her, so the two of them together could use some work. They would likely be best going their separate ways. 

Sophie and Rob

Sophie (23) of the United Kingdom leaves her bougie apartment with an indoor bathroom to be with Rob (32) in the worst part of Los Angeles.

Sophie's mom refers to Rob as "Rob the Knob," and you know what? She's right. He's awful. He is a serial (online, like that makes a difference) cheater and is emotionally manipulative. When Sophie came out to him as bi, he equated this to his cheating on her. I like Sophie. She can do waaaay better than Rob. She deserves a more supportive partner AND an indoor bathroom!

Manuel and Ashley

This couple of bozos met in Ecuador when Ashley (31) was there to study marine biology. After breaking up, the couple decided to give it another chance, with Manuel (34) leaving his financially struggling family in Ecuador to be with Ashley in the holy land of Rochester, New York.

I liked Ashley when she was first introduced. She's a self-described witch, so she's got something that sets her apart from the rest of the couples this season. Unfortunately, that's all she has going for her. She overlooks the flaming red flags that Manuel swings in front of her face. This full-grown man took to the streets during an argument and left Ashley behind. He has zero communication skills and pouts like a child.

Nick and Devin

This is the most normal couple to grace our screens. Nick (30) and Devin (23) met in Australia. After dating for three weeks, the two decided to apply for the K-1 visa. The couple got married in Devin's home state of Arkansas. 

I really don't have anything negative to say about this couple. Nick does refer to Devin as "piggy" which she has complained about, yet he continues to use as a nickname. Other than that, they actually got to know each other and work out all of the details about their future before getting married. (I should note that they applied for the K-1 visa after three weeks of knowing each other, but spent 2 years engaged.) They are the most mature couple of this season and I really hope they stay together!

Justin and The Nikki

The couple's first go at their relationship ended when Nikki (47) revealed to Justin (36) that she was transgender as a "gotcha" moment in the middle of a heated argument. For some reason, the couple got back together. Now, Justin is leaving Moldova to be with Nikki in New Jersey.

First of all, his name isn't Justin, it's Igor. Nikki renamed him Justin because when they met, she thought he looked just like Justin Timberlake. Her name is Nikki, but Justigor call her "The Nikki," which is probably some translation thing but it's so funny to me.

I wish I knew less about these two. I do not need to know the details about their intimate life. Please remove it from my brain. 

Anali and Clayton (and Closet Mom)

Anali (26) and Clayton (29) met on a language app. Without knowing many details about Clayton's living situation, Anali left her ill mother in Peru to be with her love in Kentucky. Now, Clayton and Anali live in a humble apartment with Clayton's mom, Violet, third-wheeling in a large closet.

IIIIIIIII hate these two. Clayton and Anali have zero chemistry. I can't place much blame on Anali; Clayton is the prime example of an incel, openly complaining about private details to anyone around him (i.e., the waitress at a restaurant while they were on a double date with Clayton's best friend). He spends all of his time playing RuneScape and has no social life. His mom is a hoarder and lives in a large closet in his apartment.

Citra and Sam

Citra (26) and Sam (30) met on a dating app in Indonesia. Now, Citra and her family are coming to the States to be with Sam in Missouri. However, this couple may not be united for long, as unbeknownst to Citra, Sam faces potential jail time for his drug history.

Sam gives me the ick. Citra seems nice enough. I don't really have a ton to say about them.
